And under the manuscript links,

00:45:23.439 --> 00:45:25.159
you can see the hosted version.

00:45:25.159 --> 00:45:27.679
You can go ahead and launch your own binder instance

00:45:27.679 --> 00:45:29.399
and play around with it as well,

00:45:29.399 --> 00:45:31.520
or just clone the repository.

00:45:31.520 --> 00:45:34.760
And if you like, use that as your starting point

00:45:34.760 --> 00:45:38.919
instead of the version that is on the Corto documentation.

00:45:38.919 --> 00:45:42.080
From a Corto manuscript functionality perspective,

00:45:42.080 --> 00:45:43.479
they're very similar.

00:45:43.479 --> 00:45:46.639
The difference is this is sort of in a medical context

00:45:46.639 --> 00:45:50.000
and that was in more of a geophysical context, I think.

00:45:51.000 --> 00:45:52.399
Thank you so much for listening.

